## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="161ff-1055">Lê um `XmlNode` do leitor fornecido e posições o leitor no próximo nó.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="161ff-1055">Reads one `XmlNode` from the given reader and positions the reader on the next node.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="161ff-1056">Esse método cria o tipo de `XmlNode` correspondência de <xref:System.Xml.XmlNode.NodeType%2A> no qual o leitor está posicionado no momento.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="161ff-1056">This method creates the type of `XmlNode` matching the <xref:System.Xml.XmlNode.NodeType%2A> on which the reader is currently positioned.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="161ff-1057">(Se o leitor estiver no estado inicial, `ReadNode` avança o leitor para o primeiro nó e, em seguida, opera nesse nó.)</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="161ff-1057">(If the reader is in the initial state, `ReadNode` advances the reader to the first node and then operates on that node.)</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="161ff-1058">Se o leitor está posicionado no início de um elemento, `ReadNode` lê todos os atributos e qualquer filho nós, até e incluindo a marca de fim do nó atual.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="161ff-1058">If the reader is positioned on the start of an element, `ReadNode` reads all the attributes and any child nodes, up to and including the end tag of the current node.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="161ff-1059">O `XmlNode` retornado contém subárvore que representa tudo o que ler.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="161ff-1059">The `XmlNode` returned contains the sub-tree representing everything read.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="161ff-1060">O leitor está posicionado imediatamente após a marca de fim.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="161ff-1060">The reader is positioned immediately after the end tag.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="161ff-1061">`ReadNode` também pode ler atributos, mas nesse caso, ele não avança o leitor para o próximo atributo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="161ff-1061">`ReadNode` can also read attributes, but in this case it does not advance the reader to the next attribute.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="161ff-1062">Isso permite que você escreva o código c# a seguir:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="161ff-1062">This allows you to write the following C# code:</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
XmlDocument doc = new XmlDocument();  
while (reader.MoveToNextAttribute())  
{  
  XmlNode a = doc.ReadNode(reader);  
  // Do some more processing.  
}  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="161ff-1063">`ReadNode` consumir o valor do atributo, que significa que depois de chamar `ReadNode` em um atributo <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader.ReadAttributeValue%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> retorna `false`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="161ff-1063">`ReadNode` does consume the attribute value though, which means after calling `ReadNode` on an attribute, <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader.ReadAttributeValue%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> returns `false`.</span></span>  
  
   
  
